--- !u!114 &1014062162
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1014062160}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "<size=170%><b>Prologue: Degree Meets Reality</b></size>\r\nYou are a newly
    graduated student with a <b>Bachelor of Software Engineering</b>. Not long ago,
    this path looked like a guaranteed win: booming industry, strong salaries, and
    a clear career road. You entered with confidence. Then the real world opened
    the job board. The market is crowded, competition is brutal, and \u201Centry-level\u201D
    somehow means \u201Calready experienced.\u201D Your resume, built mostly on a
    degree and optimism, is no longer enough. If you want a future in this city,
    you must build your profile from scratch, survive bad calls, and climb the only
    path that matters: <b>Startup -> Mid-tier -> Big Tech</b>.\r\n\r\n<size=150%><b>How
    Your Journey Works</b></size>\r\nThis is a role-play survival loop disguised
    as career growth. You walk around the city, interact with objects, and complete
    mini-games to improve your resume. Every successful task adds real progress.
    Every company application is a calculated risk. You only have <b>3 failed applications</b>
    before the run ends. If you lose, you restart and try again with better decisions.
    If you win, you become \u201Chigh impact talent\u201D right before the next corporate
    restructuring wave remembers your name.\r\n\r\n<size=150%><b>Market Warning</b></size>\r\nAt
    the top-right of the screen, a <b>Market Phase</b> indicator runs in a cycle.
    It reflects hiring conditions in real time. When the market is up, your application
    odds are stronger. When the market is down, even a decent resume can be rejected
    with impressive consistency. Timing is not cosmetic in this game. Timing is survival.\r\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 772f54b4818134b4a9050aea9c449a7e, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -3032622937591406102, guid: 772f54b4818134b4a9050aea9c449a7e, type: 2}
